article.headline: Georgia 92, Morehead State 42
article.linkText: Georgia gets lopsided win over Morehead St
article.story:
RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Kara Braxton had 17 points and eight
rebounds to lead No. 11 Georgia to its most lopsided win in nearly
two years, 92-42 Monday over Morehead State in the Comfort Suites
Classic.

Georgia (9-2) trailed only once, at 2-0, and scored 26 straight
points during one second-half stretch when Morehead State (3-5)
went more than eight minutes without a point.

Sherill Baker and Jessica Pierce added 16 points each for the
Bulldogs, who posted their largest winning margin since a 105-36
rout of Morris Brown on Jan. 7, 2002. Pierce also grabbed 11
rebounds, while Baker had five steals and six assists.

Megen Gearhart led Morehead State with 15 points.

Morehead State shot 24.5 percent from the field and didn't
manage baskets on consecutive possessions until the final minute of
the first half. The Eagles trailed 46-24 at halftime.

Morehead State pulled within 46-29 in the first minute of the
second half but could get no closer. Georgia led 58-36 with 12
minutes left and extended its lead to 84-36 before Morehead State
scored again.
